// EXPECTED: compile error
// free(slice) emits free() directly — holds the libc heap lock, same deadlock
// hazard as slab.free / Task.free_ptr inside @critical. The universal slice-free
// path is handled directly (never desugars to a banned method), so it needs its
// own check_isr_ban.
void main() {
    [*]u32 s = alloc(u32, 4) orelse return;
    @critical {
        free(s);
    }
}
